            {
                "s2_paper_id": "a3e245105273c7bbde8be3d255d8550877e7789a",
                "title": "Failure of a Single Varicella Vaccination to Protect Children With Cancer From Life-Threatening Breakthrough Varicella",
                "year": 2015,
                "venue": "The Pediatric Infectious Disease Journal",
                "citation_count": 11,
                "reference_count": 29,
                "abstract": "We report 2 children with life-threatening breakthrough varicella. Both had received 1 varicella vaccination before onset of cancer. Despite treatment with intravenous acyclovir, 1 child died of disseminated varicella. Because similar fatal cases have been reported, high-risk immunocompromised children with 1 varicella vaccination may warrant the same varicella prophylaxis as immunocompromised children who have never been vaccinated.",
